Challenge 6: The "Out of Memory" Assassin
Scenario: A Java application keeps crashing randomly. There are no errors in the application logs; the process simply vanishes.
The Task: 
In Linux, when RAM runs out, the kernel's OOM (Out of Memory) Killer terminates processes to save the OS. Find the system log file (in /var/log/ or via journalctl) where the kernel records its "kills". Write the exact grep command to search the system logs for OOM killer interventions.




Practice Challenge

Create a process consuming memory:

stress-ng --vm 1 --vm-bytes 95% --timeout 60s



Monitor:

free -h

and after the stress test:

journalctl -k | grep -Ei "oom|killed process"

The most useful command to remember for interviews is:

journalctl -k | grep -Ei "oom|killed process"
